ragalactic UV radiation, we predict that the total gas mass associated with\nthem is > 5 x 10^7 M$_{\\odot}$. If the gas is steadily falling towards the M33\ndisc it can provide the fuel needed to sustain a current star formation rate of\n0.5 M$_{\\odot}$ yr$^{-1}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 3 Jun 2008 15:11:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
